The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, July 29, 2004  Timeout
				 																DRAMA				 																																	 July 29 at Oxford Bookstore, 17 Park Street; 6.30 pm: The Red Curtain presents Shakespeare and the Mantle of Power (dir: Sumit Roy). The play is being staged to mark the launch of Oxford Bookstores theatre club, Dialogue.				 																																	 July 29 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Chetana presents Teesta Paarer Brittanta. Direction: Suman Mukhopadhyay.				 																																	 July 30 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Howrah Dakshinayan presents Bhitu Bhutor Bhul. Written and directed by Kunal Mukhopadhyay.				 																																	 July 31 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm: Natyaanan presents Continuity. Dir: Chandan Sen.				 																																	 July 31 at Madhusudan Mancha, 6 pm; August 1 at Girish Mancha, 3 pm amp; 6 pm: Natyaranga presents Siraj-ud Daulah, with Santu Mukherjee, Surajit Banerjee, Goutam Mukherjee, Shyamal Chakraborty and Nandita Roy Chowdhury comprising the cast. Direction: Swapan Sengupta.				 																																	 July 31 at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Bohurupee presents its latest production, Nishiddha Thikana. Director: Debesh Roychowdhury.				 																																	 August 1 at Academy of Fine Arts; 10.30 am: Ganakrishti presents its latest play, 17th July. Direction: Bratya Basu.				 																																	 August 1 at Purbasree Mancha, Bharatiyam; 6 pm: Kolkata Eso Natak Shikhi, a drama group of young enthusiasts aged five to 15, will stage three one-act plays: Maranastra (The Lethal Weapon), Dukhuramer Arupkatha (The Tale of Dukhuram) and Ekta Mather Janya (For a Playground).				 																																	 August 1 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Anya Theatre presents Nakchhabita. Direction: Bibhas Chakraborty.				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 Till July 31 at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 36C S.P. Mukherjee Road; 2 pm - 7.30 pm: Tamasha: Present Perfect  an exhibition of photographs by Sandesh Bhandare.				 																																	 Till July 30 at Gaganendra Pradarshasala; 2 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of photographs taken by Bibek Guha.				 																 Art				 																																	 Till July 31 at Chemould Art Gallery, Park Street; 10 am - 6 pm: Samantoral, in association with Ratrilekha Communication, presents an exhibition of paintings and sculptures by well-known artists.				 																																	 Till July 31 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: Paintings and sculptures by a group of talented artists.				 																																	 Till August 7 (except Sunday) at Galerie 88, 28B Shakespeare Sarani; 3 pm - 7 pm: Galerie 88 hosts the Parthasarathi Retrospective.				 																																	 Till July 30 at Chitrakoot Art Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: Paintings by Arun Goswami and Avisankar Mitra.				 																																	 Till August 15 (except Mondays) at Akar Prakar, P-238 Hindustan Park; 11 am - 8 pm: A rare collection of early drawings and etchings of K Laxma Goud.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 July 29 at Solace, 4 Sunny Park; 9 am - 8 pm: Master Hector Ramos will showcase his photographs on Nature and Travel throughout India, North America, South-East Asia and Europe.				 																																	 Till August 10 at Uma, 2/4A Sarat Bose Road (near Minto Park): British Council is hosting Global Local, an exhibition of the works of Indian designers who have imbibed British design styles in their creations. The exhibition showcases the works of at least two city designers, Sabyasachi Mukherjee and Darshan Shah, among others like Anshu Arora Sen, George Chakravarthi, Manish Arora, Maithili Ahluwalia and Abraham Thakore.				 																performing arts				 																																	 July 31 at Sujata Sadan; 6 pm: The seond phase of Tribenis annual programme, Jakhan Brishti Namlo, features Tagore songs and poems on the rainy season to be presented by its students.				 																WORKSHOP				 																																	 August 1 onwards at 6 National Library Avenue: The Creative Arts begins workshops on theatre by Ramanjit, on creative writing by Swati Lal, on advertising and communication by Arthur Cardozo, and on fine arts by Samit Dey. Details at 9830775677; 23213225				 																																	 August 3 - 8 at 1 Merlin Park (opp. Ballygunge Tram Depot); 7 am - 9.30 am amp; 6 pm - 8.30 pm: Art of Living organises a workshop (for those who are 21 and above) to prepare one to live a happy and healthy life and be able to cope with day-to-day stresses and develop self-confidence. Details at 9831023445 / 31034764.				 																TALK				 																																	 July 29 at Nandan-3; 6 pm: Mr Shahriar Kabir, eminent writer and journalist of Bangladesh, will speak on his recent visit to Tatarstan.				 																																	 July 29 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 6.15 pm: Swami Somatmananda will speak in Bengali on Swami Vivekanandas Devavani.				 																																	 July 29 at Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, 19A amp; B Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Swami Samshuddhananda will speak in Bengali on Srimad-Bhagavad.				 																ANTI-DRUG DRIVE				 																																	 July 29 at Sealdah (near railway station); 6.30 pm: As part of its anti-drug campaign, Calcutta Police, with the active participation of banglanatak.com, organises the street play, Jiban Phirey Esho.				 																POETRY				 																																	 July 30 at Srijan rooftop; 5 pm: Srijan hosts Youth Poetry Festival with the presence of and comments by poets Nawal, Shahnaz Nabi and Srijato, and those responsible for publishing poetry, Badal Basu and Chitralekha Basu. Anchor: Shiladitya Roy.
